.TH IMGMOD-SCALE4X 1 "July 7, 2026" "imgmod 2.0.0"
.SH NAME
imgmod-scale4x \- Scale an image 4x without smoothing
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B imgmod scale4x
[\fB-h\fR] [\fB-o\fR \fIOUTPUT\fR] \fIINPUT\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B imgmod scale4x
uses ImageMagick's point filter to resize an image to 400% without
antialiasing or smoothing.

When \fIOUTPUT\fR is omitted, the output path is generated from \fIINPUT\fR
with a \fB-4x\fR suffix.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h
Show usage help.
.TP
.B \-o \fIOUTPUT\fR
Write the scaled image to \fIOUTPUT\fR.
.TP
.B \-v, --version
Show the plugin name and version.
.SH OUTPUT
The command prints the output file path and reports it through
\fBimgmod_output\fR so it can be optimized by \fBimgmod -O\fR.
.SH DEPENDENCIES
.TP
.B magick
ImageMagick command used to transform the image.
.SH AUTHOR
Written by Rémino Rem: <https://remino.net/>
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR imgmod (1)
